    "verdict": "WIDTH-AXIS PRICED. Over the banked #257 verify_us(M) grid the TPS(M) curve is MONOTONE-increasing across the lambda-valid region [1..32] under BOTH step edges, so M* = 32 (the depth-9 / lambda-valid CEILING, not an interior width below 32). The #257 super-linear verify knee (M16->M32 +10.6%) is real but the rank-coverage E[T] log-growth (+14.3% per the same doubling) still OUTPACES it through M=32; the interior max sits ABOVE 32 where lambda_hat is UNMEASURED and therefore excluded (fern #249). GO/NO-GO is SPLIT by the #257 g_d step fork, NOT by width: under the MEASURED-g_d (central) step the curve tops out at 480.0 < 500 (tree-WIDTH alone CANNOT reach 500 \u2014 the gate then rests on the DEPTH axis stark #266 and/or a genuine E[T] lift fern #259/land #245), while under the ASSUMED-g_d (optimistic) step it clears 500 at M>=16 and peaks at 577.6. The E[T] anchor amplifies the same fork: only the (optimistic step x rank-cov / 4.512-anchor E[T]) corners clear; the #241 floor (4.3305) and the central step never do (3/8 corners clear). HAND-OFF to land #245: build at M*=32 (widest lambda-valid width); the gate is the g_d step-basis reconciliation + the M=32 branch-interior E[T] realization, not the choice of width. BASELINE 481.53 untouched. CPU-only analytic. NOT a launch."
  }
